               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-262-person2391">
                  THOMAS 
                  CLARK
               <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2391" type="surname" value="CLARK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2391" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2391" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Bernard's Inn, Holborn. Between eight and nine o'clock in the evening, I was in <placeName id="t18190421-262-crimeloc1462">Drury-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190421-262-crimeloc1462" type="placeName" value="Drury-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190421-262-crimeloc1462" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190421-262-off1460 t18190421-262-crimeloc1462"></join>; I was called and missed my handkerchief - it was produced to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-262-person2392">
                  THOMAS 
                  THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2392" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2392" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2392" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I was in Wych-street, and saw the prisoner following the prosecutor, who had a gentleman with him. I watched him, and saw him pull the handkerchief out a little way; he turned round to look about him - I was on the opposite side of the way. He then took it quite out; Forbes, who was with me secured him, and took it out of his bosom. I informed the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-262-person2393">
                  JOHN 
                  FORBES
               <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2393" type="surname" value="FORBES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2393" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2393" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I was with Thompson, and saw the prisoner following the prosecutor; I crossed over, and saw him take the handkerchief partly out; he then turned round looked behind him, and took it quite out - he put it in his bosom. I laid hold of him, and took it out of his bosom.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-262-person2394">
                  CHARLES 
                  JONES
               <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2394" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2394" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-262-person2394" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Forbes, and saw the handkerchief taken from the prisoner's bosom.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked it up.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18190421-262-verdict1463" type="verdictDescription">
